Y’all check out this cute personalized amp I got! It’s the @positivegrid “Spark Mini”. I had way too much fun personalizing the grille on the website. I like the idea of being able to keep my amp out for display rather than tucking it away like I usually do. You could even upload your favorite picture and use that as the grille! You can also personalize your gear settings through the Spark App where they have a TON of different amps, pedals, & presets to choose from.

Honestly a great Christmas gift ☺️ only $199 right now and they have deals going on until 12/16 ❤️💚

I first got turned on to Jeff Beck because he was my guitar teacher’s favorite. The first time I saw him live I was 16 and just started taking guitar seriously. I was blown away by his playing. My mom splurged on 3rd row tickets and at the very end I made my way to the front row.. people were throwing bouquets of flowers for him on stage, he gathered up all of the flowers off the ground and handed them to me and mouthed “thank you” & smiled. I almost passed out my heart was so happy. That was one of my favorite moments ever 💖 Rest easy @jeffbeckofficial

Happy New Year ✨ I like focusing on what I was grateful for in 2023 versus resolutions for 2024. It feels more inspiring in a gentle and empowering way rather than how resolutions make me feel pressured and anxious lol. I have a million things I was grateful for, one of them being this song I wrote “Lighthouse” that portrays mental illness through the symbolism of an east coastal storm and its lighthouse (and how storms always clear up!) I became obsessed with the idea of finishing it and recording parts in an actual lighthouse. It was so fulfilling to spend a few nights alone with the sea, singing and dancing around this lighthouse in Bristol, Maine. I felt deeply connected to nature, music, and god .. and that my friends is ART. I’m grateful to be making art. 

It was about 40° when I recorded this lil video so the audio isn’t great but it’s more for scenery and the story! If you made it this far - I’d love to know what you were grateful for in 2023 🩵

✨✨✨
